.TH _PRINTF 3 "05 Sep 2025" "1.0" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
_printf \- prints output according to a format
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf produces output according to a format string. It handles the following conversion specifiers:

.TP
%c
Prints a single character.

.TP
%s
Prints a string.

.TP
%d
Prints a signed decimal integer.

.TP
%i
Prints a signed decimal integer.

.TP
%%
Prints a percent sign.

.TP
Other characters
If an unknown specifier is used, _printf prints a percent sign followed by the unknown character.

.SH RETURN VALUE
On success, _printf returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).  
If the format string is NULL, _printf returns -1.

.SH NOTES
- Does not handle flags, field width, precision, or length modifiers.
- Output is written to the standard output (stdout).
- NULL string arguments are printed as "(null)".

.SH EXAMPLE
int len;
len = _printf("Hello %s!\n", "world");

.SH AUTHOR
Holberton School

